# Architecture Boundaries

Respect this dependency direction:

```text
core
ecs        -> core
assets     -> core
renderer   -> core, ecs, assets
physics    -> core, ecs
networking -> core, ecs
gameplay   -> core, ecs, physics, networking
editor     -> core, ecs, renderer, assets, gameplay

game_client       -> core, ecs, renderer, assets, gameplay, networking
map_editor        -> core, ecs, renderer, assets, editor
dedicated_server  -> core, ecs, gameplay, networking, physics
```

## Core rules

`core` may contain:

- logging
- assertions
- status/result types
- config
- paths
- filesystem helpers
- command-line parsing
- platform abstraction
- signal handling
- crash/terminate handling
- time/timers
- fixed timestep
- UUID
- SDL3 window wrapper
- event queue
- keyboard/mouse/gamepad input
- application loops
- job system/thread pool

`core` must not contain:

- Vulkan
- renderer
- ECS scene/entity logic
- physics
- networking
- GameNetworkingSockets
- gameplay
- hockey rules
- editor UI
- ImGui
- asset importer/cooker

## Dedicated server rules

The dedicated server:

- must be headless
- must not create a window
- must not initialize Vulkan
- must not link renderer
- must not link ImGui
- must not link editor UI
- must own authoritative simulation later
- must run fixed tick loop
- must support Ctrl+C/SIGTERM shutdown

If a requested change violates the dependency graph, stop and explain the violation before editing.
